The paper deals with active authentication using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and autoencoders for one class classification. The main focus is on face-based authentication datasets, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of CNNs and autoencoders for feature extraction and regularization respectively, suggests that the paper may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with security and privacy issues related to authentication, which may fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of datasets and evaluation metrics related to multimedia (cs.MM) suggests that this sub-category may also be relevant.
